    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello! I found that when using the ```vim.opt.cmdheight = 0``` parameter, the lualine status bar starts flickering when using nvim-cmp. I was looking for a similar error there and found it. It stated that this particular command was the problem, as it was experimental. Please fix this problem! Here is a link to that discussion: https://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-cmp/issues/1218\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAdd the standard settings for lualine, nvim-cmc to your configuration, set the parameter ```vim.opt.cmdheight = 0``` and set any lsp to receive auto-completion. For example, pyrigt.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe ```vim.opt.cmdheight = 0``` parameter should hide the command line so that there is no flicker on the status bar (lualine)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1702233742\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nmost likely, this is specific only to neovim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux stable\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkonsole 23.08.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nthe official arch repository",
